column1: TABLE II. (Part 2)  Provisional cases of selected notifiable diseases, United States, week ending April 13, 2013 (WEEK 15)*
column labels in same order that data fields appears in each record below:
Dengue Virus Infection, Dengue Fever† current week
Dengue Virus Infection, Dengue Fever† previous 52 weeks median
Dengue Virus Infection, Dengue Fever† previous 52 weeks maximum
Dengue Virus Infection, Dengue Fever† cummulative for 2013
Dengue Virus Infection, Dengue Fever† cummulative for 2012
Dengue Virus Infection, Dengue Hemorrhagic Fever § current week
Dengue Virus Infection, Dengue Hemorrhagic Fever § previous 52 weeks median
Dengue Virus Infection, Dengue Hemorrhagic Fever § previous 52 weeks maximum

C.N.M.I.: Commonwealth of Northern Mariana Islands.
* Case counts for reporting years 2012 and 2013 are provisional and subject to change.
For further information on interpretation of these data, see http://wwwn.cdc.gov/nndss/document/ProvisionalNationaNotifiableDiseasesSurveillanceData20100927.pdf.
Data for TB are displayed in Table IV, which appears quarterly.
† Dengue Fever includes cases that meet criteria for Dengue Fever with hemorrhage, other clinical, and unknown case classifications.
§ DHF includes cases that meet criteria for dengue shock syndrome (DSS), a more severe form of DHF.
